  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations in Nebraska for FY2026 to date total $902M. Obligations fell 28.8% year over year. Federal buying in the state so far includes 12,819 awards with an average award size of $70.3K; current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date). Historical annual obligations show a peak of $2B in FY23 and repeated $1.3B totals in FY21, FY22, FY24, and FY25. The largest buying agencies in FY2026 to date are the Department of Defense ($321M) and the Department of Education ($289M). The largest single vendor recipient is NELNET SERVICING LLC with $289M in obligations. Major industries by NAICS include Other Activities Related to Credit Intermediation ($289M) and Computer Systems Design Services ($154M). Other notable agency and vendor totals in FY2026 to date include the General Services Administration ($132M), GENERAL DYNAMICS INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY, INC. ($121M), and Engineering Services ($84.1M). These figures reflect fiscal-year-to-date obligations and do not represent full-year totals.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "What changed in Nebraska federal obligations year over year?",
        "body": "Obligations fell 28.8% year over year. FY26 to date spending is $902M compared with earlier full-year totals that include $2B in FY23 and $1.3B in multiple prior years. The FY2026 total is a partial, fiscal-year-to-date figure."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies and vendors account for the largest shares of FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense leads buying with $321M and the Department of Education follows with $289M. NELNET SERVICING LLC is the largest vendor with $289M, and GENERAL DYNAMICS INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY, INC. accounts for $121M. Together these agencies, vendors, and top industries such as Computer Systems Design Services ($154M) represent the largest concentration of obligations."
      }
    ]
